, 
5E–F
. Epigynal plate with distinct atrium at central part. Median septum short, as wide as spermathecae width (
Fig. 4E
). Copulatory openings small, triangular (
Fig. 5E
), located at middle part of epigynal plate, close to each other. Copulatory ducts thick, extending to vulva, gradually separating away near their ends, curving upward abruptly and connected to bursa (
Fig. 5F
). Glandular appendages digit-shaped (
Fig. 5E
); connecting tube thin, located at middle of copulatory ducts (
Fig. 5E
), connected to posterior of spermathecae. Spermathecae oval, middle size, close to each other. Fertilization ducts located on anterior margin of spermathecae.
